From b8a5becf4cba4d64a74b0f7a9eec966f4330f2c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arun Vikas T <vikast@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 13:09:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/7] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Add support for SCS request
 handling and parsing

Introduce support for processing Robust AV Streaming action
frames, specifically Stream Classification Service (SCS) requests,
as defined in IEEE 802.11 standard.

- Integrate with the action frame handler to parse SCS requests
  when the feature is enabled.
- Parsing of SCS descriptors and fields:
	- Intra Access Category element
	- TCLAS elements (Type 4 and Type 10 classifiers)
	- TCLAS processing element
	- QoS attributes

Add the following functions:
- hostapd_handle_robust_av():
Entry point for handling WLAN_ACTION_ROBUST_AV_STREAMING frames.
- hostapd_handle_scs_req():
Parses the action frame and extracts SCS descriptors.
- hostapd_parse_scs_desc():
Parses individual SCS descriptor fields including SCS ID, request type,
and optional elements.
- hostapd_parse_scs_tclas_elements():
Parses and aggregates TCLAS elements and processing elements.
- hostapd_parse_tclas4_params():
Parses TCLAS classifier type 4 (IPv4/IPv6-based flow classification).
- hostapd_parse_tclas10_params():
Parses TCLAS classifier type 10 (protocol-based filtering).
- hostapd_parse_scs_qos_attributes():
Parses QoS attributes if present (enabled under CONFIG_IEEE80211BE).

Spec-reference:
IEEE Std 802.11-2024
1. Section 11.25.2 - SCS procedures
2. 9.4.2.120 SCS Descriptor element
3. 9.4.2.326 QoS Characteristics element
4. 9.4.2.30 TCLAS element

